questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue where a Spring Boot application migrated to Java 21 Virtual Threads experiences severe performance degradation and thread starvation under high I/O load. Your thread dumps show that while the system has spawned thousands of virtual threads, the underlying carrier threads (`ForkJoinPool-1-worker-*`) are completely blocked. You locate the following code snippet in a critical path:

java
public class FinancialService {
    private final Object lock = new Object();
    @Autowired private ExternalPaymentClient paymentClient;

    public void processTransaction(String transactionId) {
        synchronized(lock) {
            // High-latency external HTTP call
            paymentClient.postTransaction(transactionId);
        }
    }
}

You are debugging a production issue where a Spring `@Transactional` service method invokes an asynchronous task using `CompletableFuture`. Users report that database updates executed inside the async block are either not committed to the database or throw a `LazyInitializationException` when accessing lazy-loaded JPA relationships.

java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    @Autowired private OrderRepository repo;

    @Transactional
    public void processOrder(Long orderId) {
        Order order = repo.findById(orderId).orElseThrow();
        CompletableFuture.runAsync(() -> {
            order.setStatus(Status.COMPLETED);
            repo.save(order); 
        });
    }
}
